raw_data.name: The Wandering Cup
raw_data.full_address: 121 W Main Ave, Gastonia, NC 28052, United States

reviews_data.review_text: Emma was amazing and understood that perfect coffee is a relaxed and calm thing. I will return

Love the wandering cup. Their matcha is amazing and the baristas are super nice/ sweet. I love coming here for a midday break or to sit and work/ study for a while. It’s usually not very noisy or crowded. I absolutely love coming to this place. They always have delicious pastries as well.
I walk half a mile every other day, rain or shine, to get coffee here
This is my favorite place to go,, everything is always clean and their coffee taste the best.
The coffee is amazing and the vegan cookies are LIFE
Stopped by this coffee shop on my way to Charlotte, NC and I absolutely loved my experience! I ordered a Shaken Espresso with Toasted Marshmallow + Caramel and it was made to perfection!

10/10 vibe!! I love the vibe that The Wandering Cup and The Alchemy has to offer and the coffee is delicious! Everything I’ve ever tried is so yummy and always brings me back and excited for my next one!
Melanie took great care of me and my employees. The coffee was just as we ordered and it was delicious.

Feels like home! Drinks and food is great and all the staff are so friendly and knowledgeable.  Great spot to grad a drink and take a break from working from home or if you are just looking for a change of scenery.

The Wandering Cup is hands-down my favorite coffee shop! Their seasonal menu is always creative and exciting, but you really can’t go wrong with anything on their regular menu either. From their perfectly balanced matcha lattes to their rich, smooth drip coffee—and everything in between—it’s always a treat.

I stop by multiple times a week, and the staff is truly what makes this place special. They know their regulars by name, remember my usual order, and always bring such a warm, welcoming energy. You can tell they’re passionate about what they do, and they’re constantly crafting new, elevated drinks to share with the community.

The Wandering Cup is more than just a coffee shop—it’s a staple in downtown Gastonia, and I’m so grateful to have them in the neighborhood!

I recently visited The Wandering Cup, and I have to say, it’s an amazing place to get a cup of coffee! The service is top-notch – the staff is friendly, welcoming, and knowledgeable. The coffee itself is incredible, with rich flavors and the perfect brew every time. If you’re looking for a cozy spot with great vibes and even better coffee, this is the place to be. Highly recommend! 5 stars all the way!
They make a great, genuine matcha latte! No sweeteners added unless you ask unlike some places. The cashier was really nice too. Will definitely come again!

One of my favorite local coffee spots! The baristas at The Wandering Cup are always so friendly, and the positive energy as soon as you walk in is unmatched.

Now, let’s talk about the coffee this is REAL coffee. Always fresh, always delicious, with plenty of options to choose from. Whether you’re in the mood for a matcha, latte, chai, or something customized, they’ve got you covered. I especially love their specialty lattes that support local nonprofits.

If you’re ever in downtown Gastonia, make sure to stop by The Wandering Cup, you won’t be disappointed! 🤩

LOVE, LOVE, LOVE! My business partner and I started out meeting weekly at the Belmont location and had such a great experience—the food, service, coffee, matcha, everything was A++. We loved it so much that we found the Gastonia location and are now part of Alchemy Co-working, which means we’re basically here every day for coffee, matcha, and snacks. It’s always consistent, and the staff never fails to brighten our day. So grateful to have Wandering Cup in Gastonia! 😊

I've been coming here since they're open, love the environment and vibe. The only thing that has changed is the temperature of the coffee. There are times when I get my coffee hot and other times lukewarm. Hopefully they can fix the temperature 🌡️
Good place n people
I always come for my coffee and cookie ❤️

I had a disappointing experience at this coffee shop. I made a small mistake while ordering—something easily corrected and for which I immediately apologized. However, the employee (older lady) was unnecessarily rude, belittling me in front of other customers instead of handling the situation professionally. What stood out even more was how much friendlier she was to the well-dressed customer after me. No one should be treated differently based on their appearance. This was the first time I’ve ever been treated this way at a coffee shop, and it was an unpleasant experience. I hope management emphasizes better customer service and fairness in the future. Would NOT recommend to anyone. Doctors, lawyers, & accountants dress down too. You never know who you are serving simply based on clothing. Never judge a book by its cover.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, Li, I’m so sorry for the experience you had during your visit to our shop. That is not even close to the experience we strive for our guests, and it’s deeply disappointing that we fell short. No guest should ever feel belittled or judged, and I sincerely apologize you felt that way. Your feedback is invaluable in helping us improve, and we would love to talk with you more about this visit. Please email me at connect@thewanderingcup.coffee so we can continue this discussion and make things right.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, great environment and staff is super nice.

Emma is the sweetest barista ever and my drink was absolutely amazing! 10/10 I love it here! I bring my friends all the time and they all love it! I get consistency with service! The care I received my first visit has remained strong throughout every visit I’ve had! If you’re contemplating coming here just go! You won’t be disappointed!
The young barista was very nice! The maple vanilla salt latte was delicious that she prepared. She had a wonderful smile and was very welcoming. I will definitely be coming back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for taking the time to leave us a review, Abigale! So glad you enjoyed your visit and our staff. Great hospitality is always our goal!

reviews_data.review_text: I was so happy this place was open this morning, as my hotel across the street had an empty thermos for coffee this morning, second time this happened to me in the last two weeks.  When I walked into Alchemy, the young Barista was working on a couple orders that were apparently placed via phone/internet.  She looked at me and politely said she would be with me in a moment.  Before I could place my order, two ladies walked in, appeared to be regulars by the conversation with the Barista, and the young lady just ignored me standing there and went straight for one of the ladies order.  I just stood there, but when she started taking the second lady’s order without saying a word to me, I turned around and left.  Everything looked really good but unfortunately I can’t comment on how good it really was as I never got to place my order.  Maybe it’s just not my morning.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, Jeff, it sounds like you may have been confused about how to place an order. We're located inside a co-working facility, so there are people coming in and out all day, some waiting to meet with those that are partners in the co-working. Not everyone who comes in is necessarily coming for coffee, so we look for our customers to be in line at the counter. I can't imagine our other guests coming in would just get in front of you to place their orders if you were standing at the counter waiting to place yours. I encourage you to come back next time you're in town so you can get the full experience of The Wandering Cup, and turn that one star into five!

Honestly, best Vanilla Latte I've ever had. Service was fast and friendly. It's small but has a nice/professional feeling. There's a small amount of free seating in the coffee shop area with a small loft up above with seating too.

Pretty stoked about my next visit so I can try even more of their options.

reviews_data.review_text:
Absolutely fantastic service and coffee. My husband and I have been looking for a good remote-work-spot coffee shop in the area and this one is AMAZING. I almost hate leaving a review because I don't want this gem taken by other WFH people! But I have to. They're worth it. They deserve every penny they get from the community.

Prices:
Reasonable/Low considering the area and specialty coffee prices. I was very pleased with this. Husband and I both got 16oz (medium) coffees. Him basic. Me specialty. The total was $10.

Coffee:
Basic Hot Vanilla Latte: Goodness gracious, the best vanilla latte I've ever tasted and of course it was my husband's drink, not mine, so I only got a few sips but there was an exquisite blend of smooth, creamy vanilla infused with rich espresso, creating a symphony of flavors that dance on my taste buds. Each sip was like a warm embrace, indulging my senses with the perfect balance of sweetness and depth. It left me craving more...but luckily I had my own coffee.

Speciality The Wanderer - Off Road Experience: I was thoroughly impressed by this coffee's rich, deep, and sweet flavor profile. It's like embarking on a journey through a flavorful landscape with every sip. The unique combination of boldness and sweetness makes it a standout choice for anyone seeking a truly indulgent coffee experience. I highly recommend it to fellow sweet lovers looking to explore new depths of flavor.
Warning, this coffee was sweeter than I was expecting. That's GREAT for someone like me who really enjoys sweet coffee (it was not too sweet for me), but I know many coffee enthusiasts who might be turned off by this. I'll definitely be ordering this again.

Service:
I was blown away by the exceptional service I received from the two women at the counter. Their warmth, efficiency, and attentiveness made my experience truly memorable. Their positive attitude and friendliness truly sets this coffee shop apart. We struck up conversation about life and coffee because I'm a chatty lady, but they were super respectful and not pushy to talk to someone that seemed not so chatty (like my husband ^_^) I'll definitely be returning, thanks to their outstanding service!

Atmosphere - Remote Work Compatibility
I was worried about this because I know it's in a remote working building, so I didn't know if there would be any free seating, but surprisingly, there is! There's a bar with about 5-6 seats down near the front counter (I didn't try these seats), and then with a short walk up a ramp behind the counter there is free seating in a  small loft area. There were 3 - 4 high tables with bar chairs and about 6 - 8 comfy armchairs seated in a circle in the center of the seating section in the loft. I'm a very chunky and short woman myself and find bar chairs very uncomfortable, generally speaking. However, these bar chairs were surprisingly comfortable, wide, and sturdy! Plenty of back support. My legs dangled, but that's expected. I could've worked there for a couple hours without getting uncomfortable. I didn't try the leather armchairs but they looked comfy and nice.

I am SO thankful that this place had free seating! I will definitely be setting up remote-shop in the future if the spots don't all get taken by the inevitable influx of WFH people who discover this place! Sometimes you just need a change of scenery!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Samantha! You made our day. Thank you so much for taking the time to leave such a detailed review and visiting us on opening day! We look forward to seeing you often!
